   HURRICANE AFFECTS GULF OF MEXICO, FLORIDA AND MIAMI
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   US CITIES along the Gulf of Mexico from Alabama to eastern Texas were on storm watch last night as Hurricane Andrew headed west after sweeping across southern Florida, causing at least eight deaths and severe property damage.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Hurricane Andrew gathered fresh strength as it moved across the Gulf of Mexico and there was concern last night that it might head towards New Orleans, which is especially low lying and could suffer severe flood damage.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   It could threaten the large concentration of offshore oil production facilities in the Gulf of Mexico.
